###############################################################################

# Steps to make archiso-avr:

pacman -S devtools

mkarchroot /tmp/pichicho base
mkarchroot -r bash /tmp/pichicho
# vi/nano /etc/pacman.d/mirrorlist 
pacman -Sy base-devel
pacman -S mkinitcpio-nfs-utils git squashfs-tools syslinux devtools cdrkit make

cd /tmp
git clone git://github.com/djgera/archiso -b avr-toolchain
cd archiso/archiso
make install
cd ../configs/avr-toolchain

./makerepo.sh

cat << FIN > /tmp/pacman.conf
[arch-avr]
Server = file:///home/arch-avr/os/$(uname -m)
FIN

make

###############################################################################

# Steps to setup archiso-avr as PXE server via NBD

1) start archiso-avr in some machine
2) login as root
3) setup your network card
4) /arch/archiso-pxe-server

Done!, now all machines with PXE enabled will boot archiso-avr live enviroment

